dc:description: Hard red micaceous clay with worn reddish brown glaze. Nozzle converging toward discus. Air hole in neck. Rim decorated by row of small stamped circles set off by grooves. Panel on either side decorated by two circles. Band set off by grooves between rim and discus. Seated lion right, in center upper half, two in lower joined by cross grooves. Base ring set off by grooves within which are five stamped circles.
